Past employment
  I have spent the last 9+ years in lighting design and sales. Whilst this has offered flexibility in my daily role it has locked me to a geographic region. It has also failed me on another approach i enjoy and that is learnign where i have felt like i have plateaud and not progressed.
The Decision
  After some deliberation at the start of 2026 wanting for a career that aligns with my interests, offers constant learning, progression & development, I came across the role of Cloud Engineer.
Walk before you run
  In order to see if this was a career for me i went down a YouTube rabbit hole, seeing what this role is, what is the day to day, what would the route into the industry be. Its enough to say its quite overwhelming, but there is one consistent piece of advice i kept seeing, know the fundamentals.
Action
  I bought a Udemy course 'Ultimate IT Fundamentals Bootcamp For Absolute Beginners'. Why this course? well it covers the basics on what topics you need to know about as well as some light coverage of the AWS console. From an overview this was the perfect taster for me to see if this career path could actually be for me.
Follow though
  I have spent the last 3 months going through the course taking it one lesson at a time, ensuring topics made sense and absorbing all the course had to offer. I'll have more on this on a later repo in more depth.
Next Steps
  I've understood the basics but now its time to get more detailed with the fundamentals and get hands on with practical labs and projects i can show and talk about.
The Goal
  Land a job as a Cloud Engineer, ideally as a fully remote role but understandably i may need to be based hybrid for an initial posting to prove myself. Longer term i would like to relocate as I see fit internationally with a career path towards Solutions Architect or Cloud Security Engineer down the line.
